msgctxt "CompareContinuousDistributions|"
msgid "Goodness of fit"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "CompareContinuousDistributions|"
msgid ""
"Compute goodness of fit tests. For most of the distributions, the default "
"tests are Cramér-von Mises and Anderson-Darling for composite null "
"hypothesis. Note that these tests rely on randomly splitting the data in two "
"sets;\t\t\t\tas a result, the results may be variable, especially for small "
"sample sizes.\t\t\t\tWhen a distribution does not have free parameters (i."
"e., all parameters are fixed), the tests are Kolmorogov-Smirnov, and Cramér-"
"von Mises and Anderson-Darling for simple null hypothesis. \t\t\t\tFor "
"normal distributions with free location and scale parameters, specific "
"versions of goodness of fit tests are computed, appropriate for this "
"setting. If the normal distribution has some parameters fixed, it is treated "
"as any other distribution."
msgstr ""

